node.statement: PART 3 - ORBIT ANALYSIS AND CONCLUSION: From traces 1.4 through 1.10, the complete mapping is: 1->7, 2->4, 3->3 (fixed), 4->6, 5->1, 6->2, 7->5. Identifying orbits: Orbit 1: 1->7->5->1 (3-cycle). Orbit 2: 2->4->6->2 (3-cycle). Orbit 3: 3->3 (fixed point). In cycle notation: [g_1, g_2] = (1 7 5)(2 4 6). IMPORTANT DISCREPANCY: The computed result (1 7 5)(2 4 6) differs from the claimed (1 2 6)(3 4 5). The computation has been verified step-by-step. Either the original claim contains an error, or a different commutator convention was intended.
